trib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":"45:437 (note).","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"html:td","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"html:span","attrib":{},"text":"Sept. 3, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/365/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–365, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"html:a","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/972"},"text":"106 Stat. 972","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In this section, the word “impose” is substituted for “assess” for consistency.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the word “further” is omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d), the words “this part, chapter 51 or 57 of this title” are substituted for “the Federal railroad safety laws, as such term is defined in ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s441/e"},"text":"section 441(e) of this title","children":[],"tail":"” because 45:441(e) is not restated as a definition."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcb0f8503-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcb0f8504-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/432"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–432","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (c) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “If an individual’s violation of this chapter or any of the laws transferred to the jurisdiction of the Secretary of Transportation by subsection (e)(1), (2), and (6)(A) of section 6 of the Department of Transportation Act, as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-06-01"},"text":"June 1, 1994","children":[],"tail":", or a regulation prescribed or order issued by the Secretary under this chapter is shown to make that individual unfit for the performance of safety-sensitive functions, the Secretary, after notice and opportunity for a hearing, may issue an order prohibiting the individual from performing safety-sensitive functions in the railroad industry for a specified period of time or until specified conditions are met. This subsection does not affect the Secretary’s authority under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s20104"},"text":"section 20104 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to act on an emergency basis.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1994—Subsec. (c). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/440"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–440","children":[],"tail":" inserted “this chapter or any of the laws transferred to the jurisdiction of the Secretary of Transportation by subsection (e)(1), (2), and (6)(A) of section 6 of the Department of Transportation Act, as in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1994-06-01"},"text":"June 1, 1994","children":[],"tail":", or” after “individual’s violation of”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
